deck: Once the lord of Lidich, he became Krampus after being bitten by Koteus.
description:
Origin

Andrzej was the lord of the town Lidich, located in Myst. He was a fair and just lord. But when a man started stealing children from his village, he tracked down the man. The man claimed the children were for Koteus, a mythic creature that lives in the woods. Andrzej lured Koteus by injuring the man. But Koteus knew he was lured and attacked Andrzej by surprise. Koteus bit Andrzej, before Andrzej managed to kill the creature. The bite slowly transformed him into Krampus, the opposite of Santa Claus, coming for the naughty children.

deck: Dead Duck was created by Jay Fosgitt for his comic Dead Duck.
description:
Origins

Dead Duck first appears in Dead Duck issue #1 in the story Soul Takers Apprentice. Dead Duck is cleaning toilets for J.P. aka Death. He then works as assistant to death, taking on his work for him. Dead Duck was born when the soul of an ancient evil being went inside of a duck, causing the duck to explode but leaving behind the egg that bore the little blue duck.

Abilities

Dead Duck wears a death cloak which seems to offer protection from death but not from pain. Dead Duck also has hidden powers he isn't fully aware of which are tied to his anger; he uses them only once to destroy a man holding his best friend Zombie Chick hostage.
name: Dead Duck

deck: The best friend and sidekick to Dead Duck, created by Jay Fosgitt for the comic Dead Duck.
description:
Origins

Zombie Chick first appears in Dead Duck in the storyline Soul Takers Apprentice. Zombie Chick is a fairly good natured character with a slightly dimwitted nature who blurts out random dialogue from time to time. She is made Dead Duck's partner to assist him in finding souls to bring to the underworld. Zombie Chick was made by pieces of other dead beauty pageant contestants and chicken scraps, hence her great figure and bird like qualities, she was made by Dead Duck's surrogate mother, Estelle.

Abilities

Zombie Chick possesses invulnerability and has shown some examples of beserker strength.
name: Zombie Chick

deck: The grim reaper himself and surrogate father to Dead Duck, J.P. is death incarnate.
description:
Origins

J.P. first appears in Dead Duck in Soul Takers Apprentice, he is the first and only grim reaper before he employs Dead Duck and soon after other beings to help pick up his slack.

Character Evolution

Prior to the appearance of Dead Duck, J.P. spent his free time carousing with beautiful women from different centuries, it would just so happen that one time when he was, he had also brought a captured spirit with him, this would prove problematic as the spirit was dangerously powerful and while he and J.P. fought, the spirit entered a duck, causing the duck to explode and produce an egg, thus giving birth to Dead Duck.

Abilities

J.P. is Death, he is immortal, able to communicate with all manner of the undead and has shown some mystical powers.
name: J.P. Yorick

deck: Assistant to J.P. Yorick, the grim reaper and surrogate mother to Dead Duck, Estelle is sweet and kind to the little blue duck, less so to her annoying boss J.P.
description:
Origins

Estelle first appears in Dead Duck in the storyline Soul Takers Apprentice. She works as the secretary to J.P. Yorick a.k.a. death a.k.a. the grim reaper.

Character Evolution

Estelle starts as a character who mainly deals with her sometimes annoying boss J.P. and has to handle his calls and paper work.

After Estelle meets Dead Duck she quickly takes on the role of his surrogate mother and seems to do so with fondness and compassion for the little blue duckling.

Estelle often has to pick up the pieces for where J.P. falls short as a father figure to Dead Duck, including his birthday party where he hopes his favorite character Big Man on Campus will arrive. Estelle takes it upon herself to play the role of Tequila, BMOC's trusted partner, much to the delight of Dead Duck who like most children is oblivious to a parental figure dressed in a costume.

Estelle's want to protect her surrogate son goes so far as to create the partner whom would become Dead Duck's best friend, Zombie Chick. Estelle does this by securing zombie parts from a store, unfortunately she discovers all that is available are pieces of dead beauty pageant contests and chicken scraps, so in a way, Estelle is mother to both Dead Duck (as a surrogate) and Zombie Chick (as her manufacturer).

Abilities

Estelle is undead but has not shown any form of mystical powers or invulnerability.
name: Estelle

deck: The first American who went into space and later went to the Moon.
description:
Commander Alan Shepard, USN was the 1st U.S. Astronaut to go into space. On May 5, 1961, Shepard piloted the Freedom 7 mission and became the second person, and the first American, to travel into space. Later in his NASA career he landed on the Moon as part of the Apollo 14 mission.

He eventually achieved the Rank of Rear Admiral in the U.S. Navy.

Portrayed by Scott Glenn in the movie, The Right Stuff.
